I. Run code in local PC
1. Install
- install python 3.10: https://www.python.org/downloads/
- pip install djangorestframework
2. Run project
- copy project to local PC: D:\project
- cmd command: cd D:\project\TodoTaskProject\TodoTasks
- cmd to run project: python manage.py runserver
- User will follow below conditions: 
      + There is a maximum limit of N tasks per user that can be added per day.
      + Different users can have different maximum daily limit.
      + Every user gets reset limit every new day.
- to open admin page:
      + username/password: danny/Foxconn168!! 
      + open browser then access link: http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin
- Using Postman
      + username/password: check in admin site
      + to post or get all record: http://127.0.0.1:8000/userrecords/
      + to put or get one record: http://127.0.0.1:8000/userrecord/

II. Unit Test
- cmd command: cd D:\project\TodoTaskProject\TodoTasks
- cmd to run test: python manage.py test
- we can run fail test -> then run pass test

II. What do you love about your solution?
This solution provides extensibility and ease of maintain. Can provide charging function to maintain and extend limit with segregation of activity permission and user data

II. Time to complete project
- This is simple project and can be complete in a day.
- We can modify and improve for more requirement if needed
